summary:
The Security Council,
 Reaffirming its previous resolutions on the International Tribunal for the Former Yugoslavia, 
Having considered letters from the Secretary-General and the President of the International Tribunal, 
Convinced of the need to enhance the powers of ad litem judges, 
Acting under Chapter VII of the Charter, 
1. Decides to amend article 13 quater of the Statute of the International Tribunal for the Former Yugoslavia and replaces it with the provisions in the annex; 
2. Decides to remain seized of the matter.

Annex 
Article 13 quater 
Status of ad litem judges 
1. During their appointment, ad litem judges shall: 
  (a) Have same terms and conditions of service as permanent judges; 
  (b) Enjoy same powers as permanent judges; 
  (c) Enjoy privileges and immunities of a judge; 
  (d) Have power to adjudicate in pre-trial proceedings in other cases. 
2. Ad litem judges shall not: 
  (a) Be eligible for election as President or Presiding Judge; 
  (b) Have power to: 
    (i) Adopt rules of procedure and evidence; 
    (ii) Review an indictment; 
    (iii) Consult with the President on certain matters.
